    #rubygroup
      %h1 More resources to help you learn Ruby and Rails

      %p After Ruby Weekend, you'll have a better understanding of how web applications are built. However, there is still going to be plenty to learn. Here are a few great resources to help you along the way.
      = link_to(image_tag("/assets/lvrug_logo_2012_white.png", class: "logo"), "http://www.meetup.com/las-vegas-ruby-on-rails")

      %h2 #{link_to("The Las Vegas Ruby User Group", "http://www.meetup.com/las-vegas-ruby-on-rails/members/")}
      %p The place to learn and share Ruby related knowledge. We meet once a week and alternate between a formal meetup with presentations and a casual hack night where projects of all languages are welcome. This is a great resource for those living in Las Vegas and we'd love to see you there!

      %p Learn more by visiting #{link_to("lvrug.org", "http://lvrug.org")} and follow us on twitter: #{link_to("@lvrug", "http://twitter.com/lvrug")}

      %h1 Documentation

      %p There are the straight docs for referencing all the details of Ruby and Rails. They might be a bit overwhelming at first, but you should be aware they exists.

      %p #{link_to("Ruby Core Documentation", "http://ruby-doc.org/core-1.9.3/")}
      %p #{link_to("Ruby Stdlib Documentation", "http://ruby-doc.org/stdlib-1.9.3/")}
      %p #{link_to("Rails Documentation", "http://api.rubyonrails.org/")}

      %h1 Great Websites

      %h3 #{link_to("Railscasts", "http://railscasts.com")}
      %p Free and paid ruby on rails screen casts. Ryan Bates has been producing content for Rails developers for several years; he's really good at teaching concepts to those new to rails. This website is a staple in the rails community. You should subscribe. :)

      %p #{link_to("http://railscasts.com", "http://railscasts.com")}


      %h3 #{link_to("Try Ruby", "http://tryruby.org/levels/1/challenges/0")}
      %p Need a refresher on the Ruby syntax? This is a great interactive tutorial which doesn't require you to install anything locally.

      %p #{link_to("http://tryruby.org/levels/1/challenges/0", "http://tryruby.org/levels/1/challenges/0")}

      %h3 #{link_to("Rails Tutorial", "http://ruby.railstutorial.org/")}
      %p Michael Hartl has put together a great resource for learning rails and it's definitely worth a look.

      %p #{link_to("http://ruby.railstutorial.org/", "http://ruby.railstutorial.org/")}

      %h3 #{link_to("Rails for Zombies", "http://railsforzombies.org/")}
      %p A fun approach to learning the basics of rails.

      %p #{link_to("http://railsforzombies.org/", "http://railsforzombies.org/")}

      %h3 #{link_to("Code School", "http://www.codeschool.com/courses")}
      %p Lots of great material here. From jQuery to Rails Best Practices. Some are free, some require payment.

      %p #{link_to("http://www.codeschool.com/courses", "http://www.codeschool.com/courses")}

